(three per …&lt;/p&gt;</summary><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Early in the year I set out to read 24 books (two per month) in 2018. I
actually blew past 24 books fairly quickly, in part due to &lt;a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/38569.Andrzej_Sapkowski"&gt;Andrzej
Sapkowski’s&lt;/a&gt;
“Witcher” series books&lt;sup id=sf-2018-books-1-back&gt;&lt;a href=#sf-2018-books-1 class=simple-footnote title="I am a huge fan of the Witcher series video games"&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; which are pretty quick reads, so I changed my goal to 36 books
(three per month).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Down to the wire, I squeezed out the last book today, December 31st. Next year
I’ll go back to 24 books and if I beat my goal, great, but 36 is a bit much
with everything else I have on my plate. I readily admit I started binging the
Harry Potter books, quick reads like the Witcher books, over the Christmas
holiday season to help get me to 36.&lt;/p&gt;
